          "id": "7ab7d05b4b7d_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7a76",
          "text": "Since the beginning in the 1950s, when people like Ludwig von Bertalanffy and Kenneth Boulding developed the field of ‘General Systems Theory’ and Norbert Wiener, Gregory Bateson and others developed the field of ‘Cybernetics’, and Jay Forrester developed ‘systems dynamics’ there have been many attempts to break free from the reductionist paradigm and develop a more holistic and systemic understanding of the complexity of the world we live in.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 141,
              "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_systems_theory",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 119,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 225,
              "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cybernetics",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 214,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 273,
              "href": "https://www.systemdynamics.org/origin-of-system-dynamics",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 257,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
